cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA. 

This paper deals with a geometric problem involving triangulated regions and paths, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of a discretized-Dijkstra wavefront algorithm implies that it may also fall under the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The problem involves weights and optimization, which could place it in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The use of approximation algorithms and optimization suggests that it may also belong to the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Finally, the use of wavefront algorithms and optimization techniques suggests that it may also fall under the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
